HEADWORD: Orleans
<hw>Or"le*ans</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from the
city of <etsep>Orl⟦eacute⟧ans</etsep>, in France.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A cloth made of worsted and cotton, -- used for wearing
apparel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A variety of the plum. See under
<er>Plum</er>.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

